properties.Title: Phoenix AZ, Carpool to Canvass in Las Vegas
properties.Description:
The Arizona Yang Gang wants to send some of our most eager & informed Yangsters out to Las Vegas to help with field canvassing before the Nevada Caucuses

We'll meet up at the Walmart Supercenter Parking Lot on 35th Ave at 6:00 AM sharp Saturday morning. Last call is at 6:30 AM so that there's enough time to knock doors on Saturday.

If you can drive other volunteers it's appreciated. Please let us know in the Group Discussion so we can connect you with other volunteers!

We hope to connect with the Vegas Yang Gang to see if they have places where our volunteers can stay for Saturday night. Otherwise we'll get a group AirBnB. Yes, that's right, the Action will continue through Sunday unless you can drive yourself back earlier!

Might be smart to bring sunscreen, water, sunglasses

Also bring food & drink for the trip if you want it (no long stops on our ride), $$$ for basic expenses in Las Vegas, wear your Yang Gang merch & bring as much Yang stuff as you can! We'll be able to get more materials in Vegas, though, so no worries if you don't have much. The Yang Gang will set you up!

If you're worried about talking to people, or don't know what to say, don't worry. We'll have training sessions and more experienced folks can buddy up with you if you need the help.

Plan to return Sunday night & it may take time to drop people off at their homes.

MUST RSVP TO JOIN CARPOOL, either here or on Facebook
Email azyanggang@gmail.com if you have questions, concerns or otherwise need direct contact

### [Call for Yang TODAY!](https://www.yang2020.com/call/)

Hey Yang Gang! Calling early state voters is one of the most impactful thing we can be doing right now to help Andrew get elected. We truly can't thank you all enough for your support and commitment to this movement.

Follow the steps below to get started:

1. Join our Yang 2020 Slack where you can chat with other callers and ask questions by [opening this link in a separate tab](https://www.yang2020.com/join-volunteer-slack/).

2. Everything you need to know about making calls can be found in our Call Team Handbook which you can check out by [opening this link in a separate tab](https://docs.google.com/document/d/17xNaWzkv6ZxpU2dQECmDFc8KcTuNj_ZOAXf9yy8jrJM/edit?usp=sharing)

We're *strongly* encouraging everyone to sign up at "peak hours" 3:00PM CT - 7:00PM CT in order to minimize the wait time between calls.
